# saneland — local Hyprland overrides
#
# Sourced from hyprland.conf (end of its Variables section), AFTER the base
# defaults and BEFORE the keybinds — so anything set here wins and is visible
# to the keybinds. This file is git-ignored: your machine-specific settings
# live here while the tracked base config stays identical for everyone.
# install.sh copies this to ~/.config/hypr/local.conf on first run; edit that
# real file (not the .example).

# --- Monitors --------------------------------------------------------------
# `hyprctl monitors` lists connected outputs, their names and modes;
# `hyprctl monitors all | grep availableModes` shows every mode an output
# supports.
#   monitor = NAME, RESOLUTION@REFRESH, POSITION, SCALE
# Examples:
# monitor = eDP-1, 2256x1504@60, 0x0, 1.5666667      # HiDPI laptop panel
# monitor = DP-1, 2560x1440@144, 1440x0, 1           # external, to the right
#
# Fractional-scale tip: use Hyprland's *exact* suggested scale from
# `hyprctl monitors`, not a rounded value — a fresh session rejects e.g. 1.5
# with "Invalid scale passed to monitor".
#
# POSITION is in LOGICAL pixels, not physical ones. To place a second output
# flush to the right of the panel above, its x is the panel's logical width —
# 2256 / 1.5666667 = 1440 — NOT its physical 2256. Get this wrong and you
# either leave a dead gap the cursor crosses invisibly, or overlap the two.
#
# PIN THE REFRESH RATE. The base config's `monitor = , preferred, auto, 1`
# wildcard takes each output's EDID-preferred mode, and plenty of 4K displays
# (TVs especially) advertise 3840x2160@30 as preferred even though the link
# does @60 fine. 30Hz reads as a laggy cursor and stuttery scrolling rather
# than as an obvious misconfiguration, so it's worth checking availableModes
# and stating @60 explicitly.

# --- App choices -----------------------------------------------------------
# Override the base defaults ($term = kitty, $browser = firefox, …):
# $term = alacritty
# $browser = chromium

# --- Extra autostarts ------------------------------------------------------
# exec-once = syncthingtray-qt6 --wait
# exec-once = nm-applet --indicator
